Keep the blur behind the dock permanent for skins that enable it (e.g. Tahoe Dark).

KWin stops blurring the dock's region once it has been occluded (a maximized
window, "Show Desktop"/Win+D, ...) and does not restore it until the surface
produces damage, so the blur intermittently vanished and never came back.

Fix, event-driven (no continuous polling):
  * plugin/backend.{h,cpp}: expose the compositor "show desktop" state via
    KWindowSystem::showingDesktopChanged, which Win+D does not reflect in the
    task model.
  * package/contents/ui/main.qml: on that signal and on task-model changes
    (open/close/maximize/minimize), re-assert the blur region every 500 ms for
    a few seconds (a "kicked" watchdog that stops itself when idle) and force a
    repaint via an imperceptible opacity nudge so KWin re-evaluates the region.
